The months with a Friday the 13th are determined by the Dominical letter (G, F, GF, etc.) of the year.
Any month that begins on a Sunday will contain a Friday the 13th, and there is at least one Friday the 13th in every calendar year.
The longest period that can occur without a Friday the 13th is fourteen months, either from July to September the following year (e.g.
in 2001/2002 and 2012/13), or from August to October in a leap year (e.g.
in 2027/28).
