Planned events on Fridays the 13th
Some events are intentionally scheduled for Friday the 13th for dramatic effect.
They include:
Resident Evil 5 will be released in the UK on Friday 13th March 2009.
Black Sabbath's eponymous debut album was released in the UK on Friday, February 13, 1970.
The Opening ceremony of Athens Olympic Games took place on Friday, August 13, 2004.
The 13th book in A Series of Unfortunate Events was released on Friday, October 13, 2006 by Lemony Snicket, also known as novelist Daniel Handler.
Four of the eleven films in the Friday the 13th (franchise) series, including the most recent (a remake of the first), were released on a Friday the 13th.
Joss Whedon's new show Dollhouse will air its pilot on the same day as above (2/13/09).
Every Friday the 13th thousands of bikers ride to the small town of Port Dover Ontario, Canada.
Natural events on Friday the 13th
Due to the large number of events that happen in the world, a similar list could be compiled for any combination of day of the month and day of the week.
Events that have been notable for being linked to the concept of Friday the 13th include:
The "Friday the 13th Storm" struck Buffalo, New York on Friday, October 13, 2006.
The asteroid 2004 MN4 will make its close encounter on Friday, April 13, 2029.
